**3. ELECTRON-3 Architecture**

**3.1 n8n Workflow Design**

ELECTRON-3 runs as a new n8n workflow triggered after the user presses
\'Publish\' on Telegram. The workflow handles video generation, QA
verification, and multi-platform publishing.

**Workflow Trigger**

When the user presses the \'Publish\' button on Telegram after reviewing
E2 content, the Brief Approval Handler currently updates the status to
\'published\'. For E3, this trigger will instead launch the video
production pipeline.

**Node Pipeline (Estimated 12-15 nodes)**

  -------- ------------------ ------------------------ ------------------------
  **\#**   **Node**           **Action**               **Output**

  1        **Webhook /        Receive publish command  brief_id, content_log_id
           Trigger**          from Telegram            

  2        **Load Content**   Fetch full content from  Script, storyboard,
                              content_logs             captions, CTA

  3        **Select Video     Route based on           Tool name + API config
           Tool**             module/platform/funnel   

  4        **Generate         Create cover image via   Thumbnail image URL
           Thumbnail**        Runway Image API         

  5        **Generate Video** Call selected tool API   Video URL / file
                              with script + storyboard 

  6        **Add Subtitles**  Burn in on-screen text   Subtitled video
                              from E2 output           

  7        **Apply Branding** Add CorpFit intro/outro, Branded video
                              logo overlay             

  8        **Technical QA**   Check resolution,        QA pass/fail
                              duration, aspect ratio   

  9        **Telegram         Send video preview +     User confirmation
           Preview**          final Publish/Redo       
                              buttons                  

  10       **Publish to       Schedule post via Buffer Post ID, scheduled time
           Buffer**           API                      

  11       **Store Publish    Log to publish_logs      Full audit record
           Log**              table in PostgreSQL      

  12       **Telegram         Send published           Done notification
           Confirmation**     confirmation with link   
  -------- ------------------ ------------------------ ------------------------

**3.2 New Database Tables**

**publish_logs Table**

Tracks every published piece with full audit trail linking back to
briefs and content.

  ---------------------- -------------- ----------------------------------------
  **Column**             **Type**       **Description**

  **id**                 SERIAL PK      Auto-increment primary key

  **content_log_id**     INT FK         Links to content_logs.id

  **brief_id**           INT FK         Links to content_briefs.id

  **video_tool**         VARCHAR(50)    Tool used (runway/pika/heygen/synthesia)

  **video_url**          TEXT           Generated video URL or file path

  **thumbnail_url**      TEXT           Generated thumbnail URL

  **video_duration**     INT            Final video duration in seconds

  **video_resolution**   VARCHAR(20)    e.g. 1080x1920

  **aspect_ratio**       VARCHAR(10)    e.g. 9:16, 16:9

  **file_size_mb**       DECIMAL        Video file size in MB

  **platform**           VARCHAR(50)    Target platform
                                        (tiktok/instagram/linkedin)

  **buffer_post_id**     VARCHAR(100)   Buffer API post ID

  **scheduled_time**     TIMESTAMP      Scheduled publish time

  **published_at**       TIMESTAMP      Actual publish time

  **publish_status**     VARCHAR(20)    scheduled/published/failed

  **qa_technical**       VARCHAR(10)    PASS or FAIL

  **qa_policy**          VARCHAR(10)    PASS or FAIL

  **caption_used**       TEXT           Which caption was used (short/long)

  **hashtags**           TEXT           Hashtags applied

  **utm_params**         TEXT           UTM tracking parameters

  **created_at**         TIMESTAMP      Row creation time

  **updated_at**         TIMESTAMP      Last update time
  ---------------------- -------------- ----------------------------------------

